@mdeuser, this is definitely a WIP. Thoughts on this method of returning the exit code? I think it could easily be translated over into the API portion of the CLI. Perhaps the proper way would be to add a new field to WskError.

Not exactly sure we want to return a 202 as that differs from the current practice of subtracting 256 from the HTTP status codes that are surfaced as exit codes.

Also, I'm expecting substantial ramifications in terms of tests that need to be updated to account for the non-zero return code.
